<body>
  <h1>StartSchool Student Agreement — Partial Scholarship</h1>
  <p class="meta">Reference: {{agreement_reference}} · Date: {{date_today}}</p>

  <p>
    This agreement is concluded between
    <strong>{{signer.name}} {{signer.surname}}</strong>, hereinafter Student,
    address at <strong>{{recipient_address}}</strong>,
    personal identity number <strong>{{signer.personal_code}}</strong>, and
    <strong>Tech Education Foundation</strong>, hereinafter StartSchool,
    address at Stabu iela 50-9, LV-1011 Rīga, Latvia, registration No.
    50008325331, represented by its member of the board Anna Andersone.
  </p>

  <p>The parties acknowledge the following:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      the purpose of StartSchool is to develop IT and entrepreneurial skills
      of the upcoming technology business leaders who are motivated to use
      these skills for advancement of their careers and of the businesses they
      work for, or businesses of their own, with a broader aim to increase the
      wellbeing of Latvian society.
    </li>
    <li>
      To achieve the purpose, several donors have contributed the funds to
      organize the StartSchool Program and to pay the cost of studies of the
      selected students. StartSchool has calculated the investment of donors
      being above €5000 to enable studying of one person completing the full
      time 12 month program;
    </li>
    <li>
      the Student has been selected as highly motivated and suitable candidate
      to receive the tuition with the StartSchool Program and as a person
      potentially capable of implementing the purpose of the StartSchool
      Program;
    </li>
    <li>
      selection of the Student over hundreds of other candidates for
      participation in the StartSchool Program is considered as the trust of
      the StartSchool Program in Student's ability to most efficiently use the
      resources that are allocated to achieve the purpose of the StartSchool
      Program and not as an award or recognition for the Student's previous
      achievements.
    </li>
    <li>
      even if the Student is paying partial or full Tuition Fee, the Student
      benefits from the environment of studies and exchange of ideas and
      opinions created by involving other students who participate in the
      StartSchool Program thanks to the support of the donors;
    </li>
    <li>
      the donors and organizers of the StartSchool Program do not intend to
      impose any legal obligation regarding Student's career choices after
      completion of the StartSchool Program, but expect Student to use the
      obtained skills and knowledge for advancement of the Student's career or
      business and the Student's commitment to increase wellbeing of Latvian
      society. Considering the above acknowledgements, the parties agree as
      follows.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>1. Subject of the Agreement</h2>
  <p>
    This agreement provides for the terms under which the Student takes part
    in the education and mentoring program organized by StartSchool
    (hereinafter StartSchool Program) and for the financial obligations of the
    Parties.
  </p>

  <h2>2. General Terms</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      The Study Period of the StartSchool Program starts on 24 August 2026 and
      ends on 20 August 2027. The Study Period ends prematurely at the moment
      of termination of the agreement.
    </li>
    <li>
      The Student shall be admitted to participation in the StartSchool
      Program during the Study Period subject to payment of the Enrolment Fee
      and partial Tuition Fee by the terms provided in Clause 3 of the
      agreement.
    </li>
    <li>
      StartSchool shall determine the content of the StartSchool Program.
      Although the StartSchool Program is generally uniform for all its
      participants and is not tailored to the needs of an individual
      participant, the specific assignments given to each participant may
      depend on the participant's previous achievements. Therefore, some
      assignments given to the Student may be different from those given to the
      other participants of the StartSchool Program.
    </li>
    <li>
      The StartSchool Program is set up as a guided and mentored self-study
      program. The Student shall invest their effort in finding and studying
      the information independently, and shall not rely solely on the
      information or materials supplied by StartSchool.
    </li>
    <li>
      The following shall be available to the Student during the Study
      Period:
      <ul>
        <li>access to StartSchool education platform and StartSchool environment;</li>
        <li>live coding sessions with professionals;</li>
        <li>site visits to tech companies;</li>
        <li>mentorship from experienced startup founders, entrepreneurs, and technology experts;</li>
        <li>lectures and workshops to gain skills and knowledge needed for building a startup;</li>
        <li>access to a workplace at StartSchool office at StartupHouse, Lastādijas iela 12 k-3, Riga, subject to pre-booking and availability of the workplace.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      During the Study Period the Student shall treat completion of the
      StartSchool Program assignments as Student's primary occupation and shall
      allocate at least 40 hours per week for work on these assignments, and
      shall take part in the StartSchool Program activities according to the
      schedule set by StartSchool. The Student hereby acknowledges that they
      have taken the necessary measures to ensure that means of subsistence are
      available to the Student during the entire Study Period, considering the
      limited time that the Student may have for income-generating activities
      during the Study Period. The Student hereby waives all claims against
      StartSchool, its officers, employees and other persons involved in the
      StartSchool Program regarding possible loss or inconvenience due to
      Student's inability to generate income during the Study Period and due to
      the possible distress related to the possibly more demanding life
      conditions during the Study Period.
    </li>
    <li>
      The Student shall use such tools, systems, platforms and other resources
      for participation in the StartSchool Program and for completion of the
      specific assignments, as StartSchool may assign. The Student shall comply
      with terms of use of these tools, systems, platforms and other resources
      as set by their providers.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>3. Tuition Fee, Scholarship, Enrolment Fee and Payment Terms</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      The full Tuition Fee for the StartSchool Program is <strong>€5000</strong>
      for the entire Study Period.
    </li>
    <li>
      For the Study Period, StartSchool assigns to the Student a
      <strong>Partial Tuition Scholarship</strong>, which is made possible
      through donations from StartSchool founders and partners, and aims to
      support motivated students with high potential to contribute to Latvia's
      tech ecosystem. The Partial Tuition Scholarship covers
      <strong>60% of the tuition fee</strong>. The Student shall pay
      <strong>€2000</strong> partial Tuition Fee and the Enrolment Fee in full.
    </li>
    <li>
      StartSchool may cancel the Tuition Scholarship due to the Student's
      sub-optimal performance as provided in Clause 4 of this Agreement, or due
      to a material breach of the Code of Conduct by the Student.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Tuition Fee payment schedule.</strong> The Student shall pay the
      part of the Tuition Fee not covered by the Tuition Scholarship in two
      instalments:
      <table class="schedule">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Instalment</th><th>Amount (EUR)</th><th>Due date</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>First instalment</td><td>€1000</td><td>Within 14 days after signing of this agreement</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Second instalment</td><td>€1000</td><td>31 January 2027</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      The Student may propose payment of the Tuition Fee in more than two
      instalments according to the schedule agreed between the Student and
      StartSchool. Agreement to such Student's proposal is at StartSchool's
      discretion. The agreement on a payment schedule other than provided in
      this clause is effective if formalized in writing and signed by the
      Student and StartSchool.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Enrolment Fee.</strong> The Student shall pay to StartSchool the
      Enrolment Fee of <strong>€500</strong> within 14 days from signing of
      this Agreement by bank transfer to the StartSchool bank account provided
      herein. The Student's failure to pay the Enrolment Fee by the deadline
      provided in this clause shall be considered as Student's withdrawal from
      this agreement.
    </li>
    <li>
      The Enrolment Fee is partial compensation of StartSchool's expenses
      related to setting up the conditions needed for the Student's
      participation in the StartSchool Program. The Enrolment Fee is
      non-refundable.
    </li>
    <li>
      All payments shall be made by bank transfer to the following account:
      <dl class="bank-block">
        <dt>Bank:</dt><dd>Swedbank AS</dd>
        <dt>SWIFT Code:</dt><dd>HABALV22</dd>
        <dt>IBAN:</dt><dd>LV90HABA0551055781933</dd>
        <dt>Beneficiary:</dt><dd>Tech Education Foundation, Nodibinājums</dd>
        <dt>Payment note:</dt><dd>Payment According to Agreement</dd>
      </dl>
      Any payment is considered made when the money is received in the
      StartSchool's bank account.
    </li>
    <li>
      If a Student requires an instalment plan, a separate written agreement
      must be concluded within 14 days from signing of this Agreement.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>4. Performance Reviews</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      Student progress and program compliance will first be evaluated at the
      end of October 2026 and thereafter monthly until the end of the Study
      Period ending in August 2027.
    </li>
    <li>
      At these checkpoints, StartSchool may assess the Student's performance
      according to the following Performance Requirements:
      <ul>
        <li>completion of mandatory assignments: all mandatory assignments must be completed;</li>
        <li>attendance in required sessions: minimum 75% of the required sessions should be attended;</li>
        <li>demonstrated progress and engagement as defined by the StartSchool Program Manager;</li>
        <li>volunteering in StartSchool organized events or activities.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      If, based on the assessment, the Student is found to have failed to meet
      the Performance Requirements and does not provide a justifiable reason
      (at StartSchool's reasonable discretion), then StartSchool may cancel the
      Scholarship assigned to the Student. StartSchool shall notify the Student
      about StartSchool's decision to cancel the Scholarship via email
      (hereinafter Cancellation Notice).
    </li>
    <li>
      After receiving the Cancellation Notice, the Student may notify
      StartSchool on the Student's intention to continue participation in the
      StartSchool Program within 14 days after receiving the Cancellation
      Notice. If the Student has so notified StartSchool, the Student shall pay
      to StartSchool, within 28 days after receiving the Cancellation Notice,
      the remaining part of the Tuition Fee, considering payments that the
      Student has already made under clause 3.4 of this Agreement. Student's
      failure to notify StartSchool of the Student's intention or to pay the
      Tuition Fee within the term provided herein is considered as the
      Student's withdrawal from this agreement, which withdrawal is effective
      without any further formalities. For the avoidance of doubt, no refund or
      reduction of the Tuition Fee will be provided for any period already
      studied under Tuition Scholarship.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>5. Consequences of Late or Non-Payment</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      If the Student delays a payment, then the Student shall pay to
      StartSchool a late payment penalty of 0.1% from the delayed payment for
      each overdue day.
    </li>
    <li>
      If the Student fails to pay within 30 days of the due date, StartSchool
      may suspend the Student's access to educational resources, mentorship,
      and facilities. If the Student fails to pay within 45 days of the due
      date, StartSchool may withdraw from the Agreement unilaterally.
    </li>
    <li>
      If the Agreement is terminated due to delay of payment, then the Tuition
      Fee already paid shall not be refunded.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>6. Suspension and Rejoining the Program</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      The Student may request StartSchool to suspend the Student's
      participation in the StartSchool Program for one year. As the Student has
      received Partial Tuition Scholarship, StartSchool may ask the Student for
      the reason of the request and may reject the request if StartSchool, at
      its reasonable opinion, does not find the reason substantial. StartSchool
      shall notify the Student on granting the suspension via email.
    </li>
    <li>
      If the Student's participation in the StartSchool Program has been
      suspended, then the performance of the obligations of the parties
      provided in this Agreement is suspended until the Student resumes the
      participation in the StartSchool Program, or this Agreement is
      terminated.
    </li>
    <li>
      The Student whose participation in the StartSchool Program has been
      suspended may resume the participation in the next year. To resume the
      Student's participation in the Program, the Student must notify
      StartSchool on resumption until August 1 of the next year. Alternatively,
      the Student may extend the suspension for another one year notifying
      StartSchool on the extension until the term provided for the notice on
      resumption. The total period of suspension may not exceed 2 years.
    </li>
    <li>
      If the Student resumes the participation in the StartSchool Program, then
      the obligations of the Parties provided in this agreement resume. The
      Student shall not be required to complete the part of the StartSchool
      Program they had completed until suspension. The Student shall pay the
      unpaid Tuition Fee instalments (if due), and their payment due dates
      shall be considered extended for the duration of the suspension.
    </li>
    <li>
      If the Student neither notifies StartSchool on resuming of the Student's
      participation, nor requests the extension by the deadline, then it is
      considered that the Student has withdrawn themself from the Agreement on
      the day when the term for notification or the resumption has expired.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>7. Further Participation After First Year</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      If the Student has not completed the StartSchool Program within the Study
      Period and wishes to continue participation beyond this period, the
      Student may ask for StartSchool's proposal for extension of the Study
      Period. StartSchool may propose the terms for the Student's further
      participation at StartSchool's discretion. The agreement on the Student's
      participation in the StartSchool Program is effective if signed by both
      parties.
    </li>
    <li>
      Notwithstanding the Student's possible continued participation in the
      StartSchool Program, this Agreement expires upon the end of the Study
      Period.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>8. Effective Date and Termination</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      The agreement is effective from the date of the last signature and is
      effective until its complete execution or until its termination.
    </li>
    <li>
      Without prejudice to StartSchool's right to withdraw from this Agreement
      provided elsewhere in this Agreement, StartSchool may withdraw from this
      agreement at any time, at will, and especially if:
      <ol type="a">
        <li>
          StartSchool considers the results of the Student's participation in
          the StartSchool Program suboptimal. Suboptimal result means that the
          Student fails to follow the program completion pace set by the
          Program Manager or participates in less than 75% of StartSchool
          mandatory sessions without a reasonable cause, or if the Student does
          not reach goals set at individual meetings.
        </li>
        <li>
          The Student does not comply with the StartSchool Code of Conduct. The
          Code of Conduct is an Annex of this Agreement and is an integral part
          of it. If the Student breaches the Code of Conduct, then StartSchool
          issues a written warning and may have a discussion with the Student
          concerning the breach. If another breach occurs, then StartSchool
          issues a written warning and the Student is invited to a Disciplinary
          Committee meeting. StartSchool may withdraw from the Agreement if the
          Disciplinary Committee so suggests after the second breach. Otherwise,
          StartSchool may withdraw from the Agreement if the Student commits the
          third breach of the Code of Conduct.
        </li>
        <li>
          The Student's further participation in the StartSchool Program is
          incompatible with the purpose of StartSchool or the StartSchool
          Program.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      Although the Student should apply their best effort to complete the
      StartSchool Program, the Student may withdraw from this agreement at any
      time, at will. When withdrawing from the agreement, the Student shall
      consider every opportunity not to do so and shall withdraw only when
      there is a substantial reason to do so. The Student shall notify
      StartSchool on withdrawal from this Agreement by sending a formal
      withdrawal notice via email to <strong>start@startschool.org</strong>. If
      the Student withdraws from the Agreement, the already paid Tuition Fee
      shall not be refunded.
    </li>
    <li>
      The withdrawing party shall notify the other party of the withdrawal by
      submitting a written and signed withdrawal notice to the other party by
      sending it to the other party's address or email address. The agreement
      is terminated on the 5th day following the dispatch of the withdrawal
      notice. The Student's payment obligations provided in this Agreement
      remain effective until fulfilment.
    </li>
    <li>
      If either StartSchool or the Student withdraws from the agreement, then
      the Enrolment Fee is not refunded.
    </li>
    <li>
      If StartSchool withdraws from this agreement at will (without referring
      to Clause 5.2 or to paragraph 8.2.a, 8.2.b or 8.2.c of this Agreement)
      and if the Student has paid Tuition Fee in advance for the period after
      the withdrawal, then StartSchool shall refund to the Student the part of
      the Tuition Fee paid for the period after the withdrawal.
    </li>
    <li>
      If StartSchool withdraws from this agreement because of the Student's
      breach of this agreement (referring to Clause 5.2 or to paragraph 8.2.a,
      8.2.b or 8.2.c of this Agreement) or if the Student withdraws from this
      agreement, and if at the time of such withdrawal the Student has not paid
      Tuition Fee in the amount due from the Student for the entire Study
      Period until the withdrawal, then the Student shall, upon StartSchool's
      request, pay the Tuition Fee due from the Student for the period until
      withdrawal from the Agreement.
    </li>
    <li>
      If the Student withdraws from the agreement after 1 month from the Study
      Period start date, or if StartSchool withdraws from this Agreement on the
      grounds specified in paragraphs 8.2.a, 8.2.b, 8.2.c, then the Student
      shall pay the StartSchool the compensation of <strong>€200</strong> for
      each month when the Student has been assigned a Tuition Scholarship
      (either full or partial), for the period starting from 1 month after the
      Study Period start date until termination of the agreement. The
      compensation is not payable for the period when the Student has not been
      assigned a Tuition Scholarship. The compensation is a partial
      compensation for StartSchool's expenses related to providing the
      possibility for the Student to participate in the StartSchool Program.
      For the avoidance of doubt, the compensation provided herein is payable
      also if the Agreement is terminated because the Student's participation in
      the StartSchool Program has not been resumed after it was suspended, and
      if the Student has not completed the StartSchool Program within the Study
      Period and has not concluded the agreement on further participation in
      the StartSchool Program.
    </li>
    <li>
      In case of withdrawal, the Student shall pay the Tuition Fee (clause 8.7)
      and compensation (clause 8.8) within 14 days upon sending of the
      StartSchool's payment request to the Student's email address. The Student
      shall pay a late payment penalty of 0.1% from the amount of the delayed
      payment per each overdue day applied to the outstanding balance.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>9. Information and Confidentiality</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      The Student shall not disclose to third parties the information about the
      process of implementation of the StartSchool Program that, if learned by
      third parties, may cause violation of other person's rights or damage to
      the reputation of StartSchool or the StartSchool Program. The Student may
      reveal the information about its participation in the StartSchool Program
      insofar as it pertains only to the Student and does not include
      information about other persons without their express consent.
    </li>
    <li>
      The Student agrees that their participation in the StartSchool Program
      activities and assignments may be recorded in photographs or on video and
      such recordings may be used to illustrate StartSchool and the StartSchool
      Program for a non-commercial purpose.
    </li>
    <li>
      The Student hereby irrevocably permits StartSchool to use for educational
      purposes and for promotion of StartSchool and the StartSchool Program any
      material that the Student has prepared or made available to StartSchool or
      the involved tutors, mentors or other StartSchool personnel, in course of
      the Student's participation in the StartSchool Program. The permission
      especially enables StartSchool to use such material for tuition of other
      StartSchool Program students. The permission is effective worldwide and
      without limitation of the term. The Student hereby acknowledges that by
      receiving the education provided by StartSchool the value whereof exceeds
      the Student's payments to StartSchool, the Student has received
      sufficient compensation for the permission stated in this clause and
      hereby waives all claims for the remuneration in relation to the
      permission granted under this clause and in relation to use of the
      material in compliance with this permission. The permission does not
      apply to the parts of such material that are expressly noted as developed
      or authored by persons other than the Student (e.g., quotes, reused
      software code, etc.).
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>10. Final Provisions</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      The relationship arising from this agreement is governed by the normative
      acts effective in the Republic of Latvia.
    </li>
    <li>
      Amendments to this agreement are effective if formalized in writing and
      signed by the parties.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Particulars of the Parties</h2>
  <p>
    The Student: email <strong>{{recipient_email}}</strong>, phone
    <strong>{{recipient_phone}}</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The StartSchool: email start@startschool.org, phone +371 28660693,
    bank: Swedbank AS, SWIFT: HABALV22,
    IBAN: LV90HABA0551055781933, Tech Education Foundation.
  </p>

  <div class="signatures">
    <h2>Signatures of the Parties</h2>
    <div class="sig-row">
      <div class="sig-label">The Student:</div>
      <div class="sig-line"></div>
